1
00:00:06,172 --> 00:00:09,426
Hey, where are you guys?
I gotta get my lighting and stuff set.

2
00:00:10,176 --> 00:00:12,053
-Hi, Ter.
-Hey.

3
00:00:14,305 --> 00:00:17,225
I had been dating Terry for a year.

4
00:00:18,476 --> 00:00:23,481
And he really wanted to make it serious
with me and live together.

5
00:00:24,107 --> 00:00:26,484
But he was getting so famous.

6
00:00:26,568 --> 00:00:29,487
Number-one sports attraction
in the world today.

7
00:00:29,571 --> 00:00:32,073
And his lifestyle was just nuts.

8
00:00:32,157 --> 00:00:33,199
Megastar.

9
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:38,580
And I said, "Well, I'm not going to move
and then have you get tired of me."

10
00:00:38,663 --> 00:00:41,791
"And I'm left with nothing.
I'm sorry, but I can't do that."

11
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:45,253
And he didn't call me
for two weeks after that.

12
00:00:45,336 --> 00:00:46,921
I was like, "God, I fucked up."

13
00:00:47,005 --> 00:00:49,841
"I should've just…
I should've just lived with the guy."

14
00:00:49,924 --> 00:00:52,594
"Darn it. Now I lost him.
Now he'll break up with me."

15
00:00:53,428 --> 00:00:56,222
And the next thing you know, he called.

16
00:00:56,306 --> 00:00:58,224
And he was kind of stiff on the phone.

17
00:00:58,308 --> 00:01:00,977
Like, "Can you fly to Oakland?
I need to talk to you."

18
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:04,355
I'm thinking, "God, here comes the ax.
Gah! I'm gonna get it in a minute."

19
00:01:04,439 --> 00:01:08,902
So we go straight to the hotel,
and he's sitting on the edge of the bed.

20
00:01:08,985 --> 00:01:12,947
And he goes,
"Linda, I don't want to lose you."

21
00:01:13,031 --> 00:01:14,199
"And I love you."

22
00:01:14,783 --> 00:01:17,660
She was life on top of life.
She was vibrant.

23
00:01:17,744 --> 00:01:21,581
And I was young and, you know,
had never met anybody like her.

24
00:01:21,664 --> 00:01:24,959
And I realized
I didn't want to be without her.

25
00:01:25,043 --> 00:01:27,921
And all of a sudden,
he's down on one knee.

26
00:01:29,130 --> 00:01:31,049
And he says, "Will you marry me?"

27
00:01:31,132 --> 00:01:33,885
"I want to marry you
and be with you for the rest of my life."

28
00:01:33,968 --> 00:01:37,639
And I was like, "Oh my God."
It was, like, such a shock.

29
00:01:37,722 --> 00:01:39,849
Like, I was like, "What?"

30
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:42,435
You know, I was like,
"You got to be kidding me."

31
00:01:42,519 --> 00:01:44,646
I'm thinking,
"Oh my God, I gotta call my mom."

32
00:01:46,731 --> 00:01:49,359
He just took me by the arm
and pulled me into him.

33
00:01:49,442 --> 00:01:51,903
He had a handlebar mustache.
I was like, "Yeah, I like that."

34
00:01:51,986 --> 00:01:57,325
And he can't wait to, like,
you know… like a little wrestling match.

35
00:01:57,408 --> 00:01:58,493
Hulk!

36
00:01:59,244 --> 00:02:01,412
Look out, here it comes! What a…

37
00:02:01,996 --> 00:02:03,081
What an explosion!

38
00:02:04,165 --> 00:02:06,751
It's more
than just a wrestling match, Mean Gene.

39
00:02:06,835 --> 00:02:09,420
I've changed my ways
and walked the straight and narrow.

40
00:02:10,004 --> 00:02:11,589
May then this love,

41
00:02:11,673 --> 00:02:15,093
with which you join your minds
and hearts today, never fade.

42
00:02:15,176 --> 00:02:18,096
The incredible Hulk Hogan.
Now the news is out.

43
00:02:18,179 --> 00:02:21,724
My life has changed completely.
I'm on one heck of a roll, man.

44
00:02:21,808 --> 00:02:25,228
I feel like I've been winning in Vegas
for the last ten years.

45
00:02:26,271 --> 00:02:27,689
There was no time for a honeymoon.

46
00:02:27,772 --> 00:02:29,983
It was, "Hurry and pack up.
We have to be in New York."

47
00:02:30,066 --> 00:02:31,192
I'm going for the gold.

48
00:02:31,276 --> 00:02:32,443
Madison Square Garden.

49
00:02:32,527 --> 00:02:36,322
The bombshell that is going
to knock this city on its ears.

50
00:02:36,406 --> 00:02:40,326
This is what I strive for, work for,
train, and say my prayers for.

51
00:02:40,910 --> 00:02:45,290
The diamond-and-gold-studded
WWE World Title belt.

52
00:02:49,836 --> 00:02:51,880
Is my old chair still in here?

53
00:02:55,967 --> 00:02:57,719
-Wow.
-Ooh.

54
00:02:57,802 --> 00:03:00,638
-History.
-All kinds of gold in here.

55
00:03:01,598 --> 00:03:04,017
Oh, I see what the jackpot is.
Right there, I already see it.

56
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:06,519
-Here it is, right here.
-Oh my God.

57
00:03:10,064 --> 00:03:11,941
Holy smokes.

58
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:15,820
These are books I kept my schedule in.

59
00:03:16,905 --> 00:03:18,031
Oh, wow. Minnesota.

60
00:03:18,907 --> 00:03:20,450
Japan.

61
00:03:20,533 --> 00:03:23,703
-Whoa, whoa. What's that right there?
-Madison Square Garden.

62
00:03:23,786 --> 00:03:28,416
Madison Square Garden. January 23rd,1984.

63
00:03:29,876 --> 00:03:31,419
Wow.

64
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:36,925
I was ready for that night
in Madison Square Garden.

65
00:03:37,967 --> 00:03:40,887
I was Hulk Hogan,
and I had my gimmick down.

66
00:03:40,970 --> 00:03:42,889
I knew exactly what I was doing.

67
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:45,225
There he is.

68
00:03:45,308 --> 00:03:46,809
Hulkamania.

69
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:50,980
And because of the political landscape,

70
00:03:51,064 --> 00:03:54,984
we knew going in
that this was a huge deal.

71
00:03:55,068 --> 00:03:58,238
Anti-Iranian feelings
kept rising across this country today

72
00:03:58,321 --> 00:03:59,697
over the hostage situation.

73
00:03:59,781 --> 00:04:02,367
More than 200 students
burned an Iranian flag

74
00:04:02,450 --> 00:04:04,994
and chanted, "Let our people go."

75
00:04:05,078 --> 00:04:07,372
I wasn't into politics in '84.

76
00:04:07,455 --> 00:04:10,416
But on the world stage, that was the news.

77
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:12,293
Iran had the American hostages.

78
00:04:12,377 --> 00:04:15,713
Blindfolded hostages
visible in the grounds.

79
00:04:18,549 --> 00:04:21,094
We're tired of being kicked around.

80
00:04:21,177 --> 00:04:23,930
I've had it. I'm furious.

81
00:04:24,013 --> 00:04:25,223
You couldn't miss it.

82
00:04:25,306 --> 00:04:28,643
Children hung out of cars
telling the Iranians to go home.

83
00:04:28,726 --> 00:04:30,311
It was like the perfect setup

84
00:04:30,395 --> 00:04:34,274
for the all-American hero Hulk Hogan
to go against the Iron Sheik.

85
00:04:34,357 --> 00:04:37,485
Hulk Hogan, the biggest American animal.

86
00:04:37,568 --> 00:04:41,864
Back in the day, the Iron Sheik
was actually the Shah of Iran's bodyguard.

87
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:44,158
We're taking the belt back to Iran

88
00:04:44,242 --> 00:04:46,953
where it rightfully belongs
and where it will stay.

89
00:04:47,036 --> 00:04:50,456
Me being an American,
the storyline meant more than wrestling.

90
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:52,750
It's good guy versus bad guy.

91
00:04:52,834 --> 00:04:56,045
The world of modern pro wrestling
draws definite lines

92
00:04:56,129 --> 00:04:59,549
between good and evil,
with the fans providing the chorus.

93
00:04:59,632 --> 00:05:02,302
Wrestling has always been a soap opera.

94
00:05:02,385 --> 00:05:05,638
It's not supposed to be nuanced.
It's not supposed to have shades of gray.

95
00:05:05,722 --> 00:05:08,474
America, ha! Bah!

96
00:05:08,558 --> 00:05:11,644
The Iron Sheik would come in and demand

97
00:05:11,728 --> 00:05:16,566
that the Iranian national anthem be played
along with "The Star-Spangled Banner."

98
00:05:16,649 --> 00:05:18,568
That's awful.

99
00:05:18,651 --> 00:05:21,738
The fans would go nuts.
They'd be booing, throwing stuff.

100
00:05:21,821 --> 00:05:24,365
It was perfect in its own weird way.

101
00:05:24,449 --> 00:05:27,952
And it would really raise
the ire of the American public.

102
00:05:28,036 --> 00:05:31,581
The incredible Hulk Hogan
has been designated

103
00:05:31,664 --> 00:05:34,125
to challenge the Sheik
for the World Championship.

104
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:36,336
I'm just glad it's finally here
this Monday night.

105
00:05:36,419 --> 00:05:40,965
These Iranians, the 52 people,
the 444 days in captivity,

106
00:05:41,049 --> 00:05:43,092
the oil embargoes, the cartels.

107
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:45,720
It'd be like putting a six-shooter
to your head

108
00:05:45,803 --> 00:05:47,472
and holding up the United States.

109
00:05:47,555 --> 00:05:50,391
It's all that together.
That's what's got the Hulkster spurred on.

110
00:05:50,475 --> 00:05:52,435
It couldn't have been better timing.

111
00:05:54,479 --> 00:05:57,440
Madison Square Garden
is very intimidating.

112
00:05:57,523 --> 00:05:59,817
The crowd reaction was so big.

113
00:05:59,901 --> 00:06:03,696
The Iron Sheik in the ring.
Madison Square Garden on its feet.

114
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:06,866
They have a lot of hate
in their hearts for this man.

115
00:06:06,949 --> 00:06:08,993
I remember that morning.
Terry was out of body.

116
00:06:09,077 --> 00:06:12,497
If you tried to talk to him,
he was not, like, my husband anymore.

117
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:16,626
He was already, yep.
Shh. In another world.

118
00:06:16,709 --> 00:06:18,169
My parents were there.

119
00:06:18,252 --> 00:06:22,548
Yeah, because my dad was very in love
with this country and our president.

120
00:06:22,632 --> 00:06:24,675
-Number 1.
-My old buddy.

121
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:25,843
Dad likes that Reagan.

122
00:06:27,303 --> 00:06:29,389
He'd never come
to any of my wrestling matches

123
00:06:29,472 --> 00:06:32,892
because he equated wrestling
with a circus performer.

124
00:06:32,975 --> 00:06:37,563
So when he came to Madison Square Garden,
it really meant something.

125
00:06:39,273 --> 00:06:41,234
It was giddy up and go time.

126
00:06:41,317 --> 00:06:46,155
It was destiny,
and I felt that fever pitch.

127
00:06:46,239 --> 00:06:49,992
I felt that fever pitch,
and I came out tearing my shirt.

128
00:06:52,161 --> 00:06:54,163
Looking and pointing.

129
00:06:54,247 --> 00:06:58,084
And just pointing, "You, the Iron Sheik…"
And just looking at the crowd.

130
00:06:58,167 --> 00:07:03,840
The incredible Hulk Hogan!

131
00:07:03,923 --> 00:07:06,509
As soon as I heard the response, I went…

132
00:07:07,802 --> 00:07:10,430
And that's why I jumped the Sheik
before the bell started.

133
00:07:11,597 --> 00:07:13,975
He didn't know I was coming.

134
00:07:15,393 --> 00:07:16,894
That was not planned at all.

135
00:07:17,770 --> 00:07:19,564
I just beat the crap out of him.

136
00:07:20,690 --> 00:07:23,317
Hulk Hogan now stands up with the Sheik

137
00:07:23,401 --> 00:07:26,362
and rams him into the top turnbuckle.

138
00:07:27,238 --> 00:07:29,615
I don't want to talk.
I want to watch the match.

139
00:07:29,699 --> 00:07:33,703
He's going up, Hulk Hogan,
and he drops the big leg on him.

140
00:07:33,786 --> 00:07:36,497
He's down for the count,
hook the leg, one, two.

141
00:07:36,581 --> 00:07:37,790
He got him!

142
00:07:43,212 --> 00:07:48,885
The winner of this bout,
and new Heavyweight Champion,

143
00:07:48,968 --> 00:07:52,930
the incredible Hulk Hogan!

144
00:07:53,723 --> 00:07:57,059
That place was so loud and so electric.

145
00:07:57,727 --> 00:07:59,729
Just totally nuts for my mom and dad

146
00:07:59,812 --> 00:08:02,773
to hear something like this
for the first time ever.

147
00:08:02,857 --> 00:08:04,901
It's just overwhelming.

148
00:08:04,984 --> 00:08:07,570
-What about your son?
-We're very proud of him.

149
00:08:07,653 --> 00:08:13,326
He's very dedicated
and a real professional and…

150
00:08:13,409 --> 00:08:16,204
-You gotta be proud of him, mom and dad.
-You know something, Mean Gene?

151
00:08:16,287 --> 00:08:18,039
Pete and Ruth
are the people that trained me

152
00:08:18,122 --> 00:08:19,582
from the day I could toddle, man.

153
00:08:19,665 --> 00:08:22,460
They're the ones that fed me
and made these 24-inch pythons.

154
00:08:22,543 --> 00:08:24,170
This is Pete's belt and Ruth's belt,

155
00:08:24,253 --> 00:08:26,422
and we're gonna
stand behind it all the way, Daddy.

156
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:28,925
It's USA and Hulkamania running wild.

157
00:08:29,008 --> 00:08:32,720
Oh, the party,
ladies and gentlemen, is going on.

158
00:08:32,803 --> 00:08:35,973
There is your new Champion of the World,
the incredible Hulk Hogan,

159
00:08:36,057 --> 00:08:37,850
kissing that coveted belt.

160
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:45,316
He never kind of got over…
the fact that I passed on a college degree

161
00:08:45,399 --> 00:08:47,860
to become
the World's Heavyweight Champion.

162
00:08:47,944 --> 00:08:49,820
But that night, he understood it.

163
00:08:49,904 --> 00:08:52,114
It was almost like a miracle,

164
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:55,076
because where he came from,
his poor upbringing,

165
00:08:55,159 --> 00:08:58,329
to look at their son holding up
that championship belt,

166
00:08:58,412 --> 00:09:00,581
just how famous he had gotten.

167
00:09:00,665 --> 00:09:03,084
So I took them out to dinner, you know.

168
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:06,921
They were very happy,
you know, my dad especially.

169
00:09:07,004 --> 00:09:08,589
He told me he was proud of me,

170
00:09:08,673 --> 00:09:10,132
said he loved me,

171
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:12,426
and that I made the right choice.

172
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:18,432
Tonight in Madison Square Garden,
the WWE Champion, Hulk Hogan.

173
00:09:18,516 --> 00:09:22,645
You know something, Vicious Vince?
I am the WWE champion, and I knew that…

174
00:09:25,064 --> 00:09:27,608
that was a major deal
in the world of wrestling.

175
00:09:27,692 --> 00:09:30,194
Hulk Hogan is about as big
as Prince in Purple Rain.

176
00:09:30,278 --> 00:09:31,904
Hulk, what in the world
are you doing here?

177
00:09:31,988 --> 00:09:34,490
It's time to train, Daddy, time to train.

178
00:09:34,574 --> 00:09:36,576
Hulkamania, Gene-a-mania,
get psyched, man.

179
00:09:36,659 --> 00:09:40,997
But professional wrestling
didn't have national television exposure,

180
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:43,457
so "pro wrestling" was a dirty word.

181
00:09:43,541 --> 00:09:45,793
No carbs, no fat,
nothing but pure protein.

182
00:09:45,876 --> 00:09:47,169
No, Hulk.

183
00:09:47,253 --> 00:09:49,630
There's not a better way to go.
Come on, Mean Gene.

184
00:09:49,714 --> 00:09:53,926
It wasn't considered
legitimate sports or entertainment.

185
00:09:54,010 --> 00:09:55,970
Come on. Come on, Gene-O.

186
00:09:56,053 --> 00:09:58,264
When you look back
at moments that are pivotal,

187
00:09:58,347 --> 00:10:03,894
moments of time that changed the industry,
you can look back to 1985.

188
00:10:03,978 --> 00:10:06,397
That changed everything going forward.

189
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:08,357
It's ours, brother. It's ours.

190
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:13,571
In my crystal ball, I saw I was more
than just a wrestler, you know?

191
00:10:13,654 --> 00:10:16,032
This was just a setup for what's next.

192
00:10:16,115 --> 00:10:19,952
WrestleMania, what the world has come to.

193
00:10:20,036 --> 00:10:23,372
Vince, being the businessman, says,
"Hey, man, we need a Super Bowl."

194
00:10:24,624 --> 00:10:28,461
All the top talent
assembled under one roof.

195
00:10:28,544 --> 00:10:31,797
The coliseum of wrestling,
Madison Square Garden.

196
00:10:31,881 --> 00:10:35,176
In our industry, WrestleMania I

197
00:10:35,259 --> 00:10:40,056
was the most important event
that has ever taken place.

198
00:10:40,139 --> 00:10:43,267
Locations coast-to-coast
in which you can see WrestleMania…

199
00:10:43,351 --> 00:10:47,063
This was everywhere
on closed-circuit television.

200
00:10:47,146 --> 00:10:49,482
I was a little reluctant
to do a wrestling story.

201
00:10:49,565 --> 00:10:52,443
Why would a sophisticated
young audience buy into this stuff?

202
00:10:52,526 --> 00:10:56,739
It was very simple.
They had a cavalcade of celebrities.

203
00:10:56,822 --> 00:11:00,534
I'd like to talk a bit about Cyndi Lauper
for my main man, Mr. T!

204
00:11:03,204 --> 00:11:05,164
Mr. T!

205
00:11:06,374 --> 00:11:08,334
During the '80s, he was the guy.

206
00:11:08,417 --> 00:11:10,294
Teamin' up with Mr. T!

207
00:11:10,378 --> 00:11:13,339
He was the top television star
in the United States.

208
00:11:13,422 --> 00:11:18,052
Oh, wow! Now, that'll start some scandals.
Nah! Uh-huh!

209
00:11:18,135 --> 00:11:20,971
The original idea was a tag match.

210
00:11:21,055 --> 00:11:24,934
Hulk Hogan and Mr. T
versus Mr. Wonderful and Roddy Piper.

211
00:11:25,017 --> 00:11:27,353
I thought to myself,
"What is he doing fighting me?"

212
00:11:27,436 --> 00:11:30,690
Mr. T, the wonderful human being.

213
00:11:30,773 --> 00:11:33,150
Good versus evil. Plain and simple.

214
00:11:33,234 --> 00:11:35,236
You could wind up looking like this.

215
00:11:35,319 --> 00:11:38,280
I painted this myself,
with your arm in a cast.

216
00:11:38,364 --> 00:11:42,868
The hope was that fans
were not just watching for wrestling.

217
00:11:42,952 --> 00:11:45,371
They were watching for the spectacle.

218
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:53,087
That said, there was a lot of uncertainty

219
00:11:53,170 --> 00:11:57,049
about whether WrestleMania
would really fly.

220
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:58,676
There was a lot of risk

221
00:11:58,759 --> 00:12:01,637
because it was extremely expensive
to put on.

222
00:12:01,721 --> 00:12:02,888
We bet the farm.

223
00:12:02,972 --> 00:12:04,932
How's the audio sound on this?

224
00:12:05,015 --> 00:12:06,809
What kind of audio do you have?

225
00:12:06,892 --> 00:12:09,520
Vince's livelihood, everything he owned.

226
00:12:09,603 --> 00:12:12,732
He begged, borrowed, and stealed.
His house was on the line.

227
00:12:12,815 --> 00:12:14,775
So much of it was built around me.

228
00:12:15,443 --> 00:12:19,780
The showcase of this business
had to be a win-win situation.

229
00:12:19,864 --> 00:12:22,491
-We've got all kinds of stuff to do.
-Back up, please.

230
00:12:23,492 --> 00:12:26,495
It was non-stop press, 24/7.

231
00:12:28,205 --> 00:12:30,207
Waiting for the break of day…

232
00:12:30,291 --> 00:12:32,918
A wrestling veteran
teams up with a rookie of the ring.

233
00:12:33,002 --> 00:12:36,589
-Ain't no telling what I might do.
-Street fighting, Chicago-style shuffling.

234
00:12:36,672 --> 00:12:39,091
Mr. T and Hulk
will be in Los Angeles on the 19th.

235
00:12:39,175 --> 00:12:41,802
Then from there,
we're gonna have to swing down to Phoenix

236
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:44,430
to do some PR for March 31st.

237
00:12:44,513 --> 00:12:47,433
Just think about Piper and Orndorff.

238
00:12:47,516 --> 00:12:49,226
Just think about that.

239
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:50,770
Just think.

240
00:12:50,853 --> 00:12:52,563
Just think.

241
00:12:52,646 --> 00:12:54,273
Just think.

242
00:13:00,488 --> 00:13:04,033
You know, when you laugh,
your little things go bambi, bambi, bambi.

243
00:13:05,326 --> 00:13:08,329
Wrestling's always been around,
but now the people are following it.

244
00:13:08,412 --> 00:13:10,539
A lot of, like you said,
Wall Street people

245
00:13:10,623 --> 00:13:12,625
or normal people
that may have been afraid to say,

246
00:13:12,708 --> 00:13:15,002
"I was at matches
Friday and Saturday with my kids."

247
00:13:15,085 --> 00:13:19,256
We were browbeating ourselves to death.
We could leave no stone unturned.

248
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:21,175
-Come on, Hulk.
-Get hungry.

249
00:13:21,258 --> 00:13:23,552
-That's what we do.
-Take that, New York City.

250
00:13:24,553 --> 00:13:26,388
I was completely beat up.

251
00:13:26,472 --> 00:13:29,642
You gentlemen have
one million viewers paying a lot of money.

252
00:13:29,725 --> 00:13:31,852
I think you should be nervous.

253
00:13:31,936 --> 00:13:34,605
I was completely spent.

254
00:13:37,149 --> 00:13:39,819
Five days before WrestleMania,

255
00:13:39,902 --> 00:13:43,489
Vince goes, "Hey, you got
one more thing you gotta do tonight."

256
00:13:43,572 --> 00:13:47,993
"Somebody booked you on a show called
Hot Properties with Richard Belzer."

257
00:13:48,077 --> 00:13:52,081
"And there's like six or seven kids
waiting there in wheelchairs."

258
00:13:55,626 --> 00:13:58,337
I said, "Okay, I'll go."
So we get to Hot Properties…

259
00:13:58,420 --> 00:14:00,214
Show me one of the moves you use.

260
00:14:00,798 --> 00:14:03,092
…there are no kids in wheelchairs.

261
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:05,678
That didn't sit well with T or me.

262
00:14:05,761 --> 00:14:06,971
What's your famous move?

263
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:09,473
I'm gonna have
to stick to the basics with you.

264
00:14:09,557 --> 00:14:11,559
The floor is hard.
I don't want you getting hurt.

265
00:14:11,642 --> 00:14:13,853
-There's--
-I don't want you hurt, so be careful.

266
00:14:13,936 --> 00:14:15,354
Belzer was condescending.

267
00:14:15,437 --> 00:14:17,523
Nice and easy if you bend over--

268
00:14:17,606 --> 00:14:18,649
No, I'm sorry.

269
00:14:18,732 --> 00:14:20,776
"Oh. Now look at this asshole."

270
00:14:20,860 --> 00:14:23,112
Just tell me, brother,
when you want him to quit squealing.

271
00:14:23,195 --> 00:14:24,530
All right.

272
00:14:24,613 --> 00:14:27,825
I'm sitting in the audience,
and Terry's like, "This guy's a wise guy."

273
00:14:27,908 --> 00:14:30,202
He's popping off
about how fake this shit is.

274
00:14:30,286 --> 00:14:32,913
Hey, fun and games.
Fake wrestling? Oh, really?

275
00:14:32,997 --> 00:14:36,125
-How about it, T?
-Keep him like that for a while.

276
00:14:41,338 --> 00:14:43,048
He's all right. He's just sleeping.

277
00:14:43,132 --> 00:14:45,718
He's sleeping. Really.
That was a sleeper hold.

278
00:14:45,801 --> 00:14:51,181
I don't think Terry intended to actually,
like, make him pass out to that point.

279
00:14:51,265 --> 00:14:53,893
But he did,
because he's, like, skinny, you know.

280
00:14:53,976 --> 00:14:55,269
Yeah, I knew I went too far.

281
00:14:55,352 --> 00:14:58,022
-He's waking up now.
-You all right, brother?

282
00:15:01,066 --> 00:15:02,902
See? It works.

283
00:15:02,985 --> 00:15:04,111
All right, brother.

284
00:15:04,194 --> 00:15:08,741
And now, we'll be right back
after this word from you-know-who.

285
00:15:08,824 --> 00:15:12,536
I went backstage and collapsed,
and the ambulance took me to Cedars-Sinai,

286
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:15,164
where I have eight stitches
in the back of my head.

287
00:15:15,247 --> 00:15:17,333
Belzer became a real pain in the ass.

288
00:15:17,917 --> 00:15:21,170
You know, I'm in show business.
I don't have a show to get almost killed.

289
00:15:21,253 --> 00:15:23,130
I assume he didn't apologize?

290
00:15:23,213 --> 00:15:24,465
He didn't feel bad at all.

291
00:15:24,548 --> 00:15:28,552
Somebody wants to, you know,
make fun of the business that he's in,

292
00:15:28,636 --> 00:15:31,764
that he's worked so hard to be in,
kind of spit on it, in a way?

293
00:15:31,847 --> 00:15:34,558
There's very little remorse,
unfortunately.

294
00:15:34,642 --> 00:15:36,477
Sure enough, a couple days later,

295
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:39,063
here comes
the half-a-million-dollar lawsuit.

296
00:15:39,146 --> 00:15:41,899
Financially,
there's going to be a big problem.

297
00:15:41,982 --> 00:15:45,235
We lived on about $3,500 a month.

298
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:50,616
We were living in an apartment,
which was, like, in the hood of Stamford.

299
00:15:50,699 --> 00:15:53,994
And I said,
"Terry, train, say your prayers."

300
00:15:54,078 --> 00:15:56,288
Pray to God WrestleMania works,

301
00:15:56,372 --> 00:15:59,166
and it's not the biggest flop
ever in the business.

302
00:16:00,042 --> 00:16:01,752
"Okay." You know?

303
00:16:03,587 --> 00:16:07,675
The wrestling extravaganza
of all time, WrestleMania.

304
00:16:07,758 --> 00:16:10,260
-What are you so excited about?
-This is WrestleMania.

305
00:16:10,344 --> 00:16:12,721
-Body slam!
-Yeah! Yeah!

306
00:16:12,805 --> 00:16:15,557
Tickets for Sunday's sold-out
tag team brawl at the Garden

307
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:18,310
have been going for as much as $100 a pop.

308
00:16:18,394 --> 00:16:21,313
Next thing you know, they'll be hawking
Perrier and quiche at ringside.

309
00:16:21,397 --> 00:16:24,441
This is where it's at.
Forget the Super Bowl, it's super boring.

310
00:16:24,525 --> 00:16:25,526
This is exciting.

311
00:16:25,609 --> 00:16:27,820
Never saw a wrestling match in my life.

312
00:16:27,903 --> 00:16:29,822
-You're about to.
-Yes, sir.

313
00:16:33,158 --> 00:16:35,577
Our main event.

314
00:16:36,578 --> 00:16:38,163
Liberace.

315
00:16:38,247 --> 00:16:41,625
There he is, the greatest, Muhammad Ali.

316
00:16:41,709 --> 00:16:43,877
Have you ever seen such pandemonium?

317
00:16:43,961 --> 00:16:46,422
It's just so exciting,
I just don't know what to say.

318
00:16:57,558 --> 00:16:59,518
There goes the bell!

319
00:16:59,601 --> 00:17:01,478
Look at the bell by Liberace.

320
00:17:01,562 --> 00:17:03,439
Oh, look at that bell, Jeff.

321
00:17:03,522 --> 00:17:05,733
Oh, nice fireman's carry.

322
00:17:05,816 --> 00:17:07,526
What's he gonna do with him?

323
00:17:07,609 --> 00:17:10,320
A slam by Mr. T, as Piper goes down.

324
00:17:10,404 --> 00:17:12,531
Whoa! Here comes the Hulk.

325
00:17:12,614 --> 00:17:14,742
All four going at it in the corner.

326
00:17:14,825 --> 00:17:16,493
And a four-way is going on.

327
00:17:16,577 --> 00:17:18,662
Muhammad Ali is getting into the ring.

328
00:17:18,746 --> 00:17:20,748
Ali stepped right in there.

329
00:17:20,831 --> 00:17:25,502
Look at Ali, took a shot at Piper.
Ali won't take anything from anybody.

330
00:17:25,586 --> 00:17:27,379
A champion taking control.

331
00:17:27,463 --> 00:17:29,339
Look out, knocker.

332
00:17:30,507 --> 00:17:33,260
Double whip now. Piper off the ropes.

333
00:17:33,343 --> 00:17:34,303
Oh no!

334
00:17:34,386 --> 00:17:37,181
We tore the house down
and accomplished the mission.

335
00:17:38,849 --> 00:17:41,351
Unbelievable,
pandemonium here in the Garden.

336
00:17:41,435 --> 00:17:43,562
He tries to pin him.

337
00:17:43,645 --> 00:17:45,272
He got out.

338
00:17:47,649 --> 00:17:51,236
Madison Square Garden,
WrestleMania, Hulk Hogan, Mr. T.

339
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:53,989
We reign supreme. Can you dig that?

340
00:17:54,073 --> 00:17:56,909
-I can dig it. Proving conclusively…
-I love it, man. Thank you.

341
00:17:56,992 --> 00:18:00,704
The whole United States was watching,
and it… it changed.

342
00:18:00,788 --> 00:18:04,875
It changed our lives, changed wrestling,
it changed everything from that night on.

343
00:18:04,958 --> 00:18:06,794
It was never the same.

344
00:18:07,503 --> 00:18:09,797
That's it, mainstream, overnight.

345
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:12,466
I'm a real wild one, wild one
Wild one, wild one

346
00:18:14,676 --> 00:18:16,095
Ladies and gentlemen,

347
00:18:16,178 --> 00:18:18,388
Heavyweight Champion of the World,
Mr. Hulk Hogan.

348
00:18:18,472 --> 00:18:21,934
That was the beginning
of this global juggernaut.

349
00:18:22,017 --> 00:18:26,021
And here he is,
in all his glory, Hulk Hogan.

350
00:18:26,105 --> 00:18:28,232
It was just total insanity.

351
00:18:28,315 --> 00:18:29,942
Move over, Mr. T and Rambo.

352
00:18:30,025 --> 00:18:33,946
It seems Hulk Hogan is now
the superhero America chooses.

353
00:18:34,029 --> 00:18:36,782
I want your autograph. You look famous.

354
00:18:36,865 --> 00:18:40,160
I just had to sit back
and shake my head and think, like…

355
00:18:40,244 --> 00:18:42,538
"I cannot believe that this has happened."

356
00:18:42,621 --> 00:18:45,582
That I've gotta be a wild one

357
00:18:45,666 --> 00:18:49,586
Our bookkeeper called us,
and he goes, "Are you sitting down?"

358
00:18:50,295 --> 00:18:52,297
Oh, look at that!

359
00:18:52,381 --> 00:18:54,800
You guys have a million dollars
in your bank account.

360
00:18:54,883 --> 00:18:58,053
Baby, I'm a real wild child

361
00:18:59,054 --> 00:19:01,056
I was like, "Terry, we're millionaires."

362
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:02,099
We celebrated.

363
00:19:02,182 --> 00:19:03,517
We just got it on, right?

364
00:19:04,601 --> 00:19:09,231
Well, Terry's new boat is finally here.
He's probably just jumping for joy.

365
00:19:09,314 --> 00:19:11,150
These girls are gonna have a good time.

366
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:13,360
Yeah, let's party!

367
00:19:15,279 --> 00:19:17,823
Professional wrestling.
It's always been popular,

368
00:19:17,906 --> 00:19:20,576
but lately, it's been emerging
from second-rate arenas

369
00:19:20,659 --> 00:19:23,453
to attract a whole new generation of fans.

370
00:19:23,537 --> 00:19:27,332
Along with Vince McMahon,
we got the beer drinkers, cigar smokers,

371
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:29,918
and bloodthirsty people
out of the front row,

372
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:31,628
and the families showed up.

373
00:19:31,712 --> 00:19:34,923
Gonna tell them all I'm a wild one

374
00:19:35,007 --> 00:19:37,009
Ooh, yeah, I'm a wild one

375
00:19:37,092 --> 00:19:41,138
Every city, every arena, I dominated.

376
00:19:41,221 --> 00:19:42,890
What do you think, Mom?

377
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:46,935
Now, I love Hulk Hogan.
My daddy's crazy about him.

378
00:19:58,864 --> 00:20:02,784
It's showbiz, pure and simple,
and America is eating it up.

379
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:06,622
I'm a wild one

380
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:10,209
So it changed the dynamics of the business

381
00:20:10,292 --> 00:20:14,421
from a territorial status
to stadiums and big arenas.

382
00:20:14,504 --> 00:20:16,506
And then the groundwork was laid

383
00:20:16,590 --> 00:20:20,260
for a lot of the other wrestlers
to jump on that train,

384
00:20:20,344 --> 00:20:22,304
cutting these guys better deals.

385
00:20:22,387 --> 00:20:23,931
So now, at the end of the year,

386
00:20:24,014 --> 00:20:27,809
instead of bringing home
half a million bucks to wife and kids,

387
00:20:27,893 --> 00:20:30,896
you're probably gonna bring
three or four million dollars home.

388
00:20:33,273 --> 00:20:35,484
He was the golden goose.

389
00:20:37,110 --> 00:20:40,197
You knew if he was on the card,
the building was sold out.

390
00:20:41,490 --> 00:20:44,076
Jake "The Snake" Roberts!

391
00:20:44,159 --> 00:20:47,037
Look at that snake!
He's wrapping it all around his throat!

392
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:49,706
You wanted to wrestle Hogan.
That's where the money was at.

393
00:20:49,790 --> 00:20:53,418
A lot of people want a piece of you,
and they all want this right here.

394
00:20:53,502 --> 00:20:56,880
Hogan meant money.
That meant you were the main event.

395
00:20:57,631 --> 00:21:00,050
That meant you got the bigger check.

396
00:21:00,133 --> 00:21:01,593
Not as big as his.

397
00:21:01,677 --> 00:21:04,888
But let's give the credit where it's due.

398
00:21:04,972 --> 00:21:08,058
Everybody in the dressing room
was praying and crossing their fingers.

399
00:21:08,141 --> 00:21:10,435
When they handed out the booking sheets,
you'd look and see

400
00:21:10,519 --> 00:21:12,521
if you were on the same shows
that Hulk was on.

401
00:21:12,604 --> 00:21:15,232
Look at all the guys
that are lining up behind this guy.

402
00:21:15,315 --> 00:21:16,400
They want this guy!

403
00:21:16,483 --> 00:21:18,402
You get a better check
when it was sold out.

404
00:21:18,485 --> 00:21:21,363
This is easy money, baby.

405
00:21:21,446 --> 00:21:23,740
Oh my God, a different level.
Are you kidding me?

406
00:21:23,824 --> 00:21:26,702
Here you're with a guy
that's making the whole company money.

407
00:21:27,452 --> 00:21:32,249
Hulkamania elevated wrestling to a place
that nobody ever thought it would go.

408
00:21:32,332 --> 00:21:33,458
This mega business.

409
00:21:33,542 --> 00:21:38,797
They say money is the root of all evil.
Well, I'm here to tell you that it's not.

410
00:21:38,880 --> 00:21:42,301
Not that money means everything,
and it doesn't.

411
00:21:42,384 --> 00:21:44,594
Only thing it does
is make things a little easier.

412
00:21:44,678 --> 00:21:46,847
We have a 12-foot surfboard here.

413
00:21:46,930 --> 00:21:49,599
Turn around, Terry,
let me see your face with it.

414
00:21:49,683 --> 00:21:51,476
The Hulkster board.

415
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:54,021
-Yeah.
-Matches the motorcycle.

416
00:21:54,604 --> 00:21:57,482
When he'd give gifts,
he wasn't a cheap miser.

417
00:21:57,566 --> 00:21:59,901
He really rolled the dice on things,
you know?

418
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:06,783
Linda and I used
to go out on the boat every day.

419
00:22:06,867 --> 00:22:10,662
It was just raising holy hell,
Wild Wild West, winging it, you know?

420
00:22:10,746 --> 00:22:14,416
It was like constant good times.
Nothing really got us down.

421
00:22:15,917 --> 00:22:18,503
Hey, Tony, what's happening, mama?

422
00:22:18,587 --> 00:22:23,925
The success and the money
turned into a lifestyle of partying.

423
00:22:24,009 --> 00:22:25,302
Good, good. How are you doing?

424
00:22:25,385 --> 00:22:29,097
-Your menu for this evening.
-Okay! You have to hand them out.

425
00:22:29,181 --> 00:22:32,059
We were running pretty hard
doing the drug stuff.

426
00:22:32,142 --> 00:22:33,602
Party's beginning!

427
00:22:34,853 --> 00:22:36,897
Coke? Yeah, we did a little bit of it.

428
00:22:36,980 --> 00:22:41,234
And we have Hulkamania himself,
with a buzz on.

429
00:22:41,318 --> 00:22:43,278
We were going 90 miles an hour,

430
00:22:43,987 --> 00:22:46,656
and, uh, whatever you think about,
we did it.

431
00:22:46,740 --> 00:22:48,200
Yes, we do!

432
00:22:50,369 --> 00:22:52,037
It was all there for the taking.

433
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:55,332
The boat's on the way back.
Okay, so what shall we have?

434
00:22:56,625 --> 00:22:59,753
Sure, I'll take a little bit of that.
Uppers, downers, sideways.

435
00:23:01,838 --> 00:23:03,799
I had diet pills from my mom's doctor.

436
00:23:03,882 --> 00:23:08,637
What we have got to face every night,
each and every night, it is a nightmare.

437
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:09,763
I mean, you needed it.

438
00:23:09,846 --> 00:23:13,016
You've got a 13 or 15-hour day
ahead of you.

439
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:15,477
But, Hulk, they all want you!
They all want you!

440
00:23:15,560 --> 00:23:19,147
When you're on one hour of sleep,
you've gotta figure out how to do it.

441
00:23:19,231 --> 00:23:21,316
Scratching, clawing, fighting.

442
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:26,405
Working longer, working harder,
to achieve a goal of greatness.

443
00:23:26,488 --> 00:23:31,159
He was kind of like "the guy."
You don't want anything to mess that up.

444
00:23:33,620 --> 00:23:35,247
And something happened

445
00:23:35,330 --> 00:23:37,749
that kind of, like,
knocked me off my pedestal.

446
00:23:40,794 --> 00:23:44,005
We were at Gold's Gym
on, uh, Sherman Way in the Valley.

447
00:23:44,089 --> 00:23:47,300
There was a Gold's Gym there
years ago, and…

448
00:23:47,384 --> 00:23:51,388
I went back out to the car to go
get water or something, or my towel.

449
00:23:51,471 --> 00:23:52,389
As I go out there,

450
00:23:52,472 --> 00:23:55,475
there's this big biker guy
just standing around our car.

451
00:23:59,521 --> 00:24:02,232
Then I looked at him,
like, "It looks just like Terry."

452
00:24:02,315 --> 00:24:06,403
The same face, the same nose.
They were twins.

453
00:24:06,486 --> 00:24:09,364
And Linda, she came back in,
her eyes were huge.

454
00:24:09,448 --> 00:24:12,659
She goes, "There's this monster
sitting on the hood of your car."

455
00:24:12,742 --> 00:24:14,119
"He says he's your brother."

456
00:24:15,662 --> 00:24:17,747
It was my brother, Allan.

457
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:20,250
We weren't that close.

458
00:24:21,001 --> 00:24:23,628
He rode off the reservation early.

459
00:24:23,712 --> 00:24:25,380
Grew up really fast.

460
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:31,011
By the time he was 17,
he was riding with a bunch of bikers.

461
00:24:31,094 --> 00:24:34,598
He got in some trouble here in Florida.

462
00:24:37,392 --> 00:24:40,479
And he ended up in Oakland, California.

463
00:24:41,813 --> 00:24:44,941
So when I used to wrestle
at the Oakland Coliseum or the Cow Palace,

464
00:24:45,025 --> 00:24:48,361
he'd always show up
with like ten Hell's Angels.

465
00:24:50,280 --> 00:24:54,493
So we talked and stuff,
and he goes, "I just got out of rehab."

466
00:24:54,576 --> 00:24:58,205
He just had a problem with drugs.
You know, hard drinking, hard living.

467
00:24:59,206 --> 00:25:02,876
You know, so Terry kind of put
the straight line on him, you know.

468
00:25:02,959 --> 00:25:06,004
I said, "Look, I'm gonna wrestle.
We'll be out there about 9:30.

469
00:25:06,087 --> 00:25:08,256
We'll jump on a plane. Come with me."

470
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:11,176
I was trying to help him out
as much as I could.

471
00:25:11,259 --> 00:25:14,054
But he goes, "Oh, no, no, man.
I gotta pay my rent."

472
00:25:14,137 --> 00:25:16,097
"I need you to lend me some money."

473
00:25:16,181 --> 00:25:19,476
So I gave him some money,
and I didn't take him with me.

474
00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:23,480
And I went to wrestle.

475
00:25:23,563 --> 00:25:26,399
And when I came out of the ring,
I got a… a number.

476
00:25:26,483 --> 00:25:28,985
And it was like, uh, an emergency, so…

477
00:25:30,487 --> 00:25:34,699
I called the number, and they said,
"Your brother overdosed and passed away."

478
00:25:34,783 --> 00:25:37,369
So I should have taken him with me,

479
00:25:37,452 --> 00:25:39,788
um, instead of giving him the money.

480
00:25:40,789 --> 00:25:43,041
So that was the last time I saw him.

481
00:25:45,961 --> 00:25:47,462
It was a…

482
00:25:48,338 --> 00:25:50,173
That was a hard one to get over.

483
00:25:55,095 --> 00:25:56,888
Was there a funeral?

484
00:25:56,972 --> 00:26:00,016
I tried to go,
but I had to leave right away.

485
00:26:00,100 --> 00:26:01,434
I couldn't handle it.

486
00:26:04,271 --> 00:26:06,731
-And your parents?
-No.

487
00:26:07,732 --> 00:26:11,695
Did you talk to them
about his death? Or have any grieving?

488
00:26:11,778 --> 00:26:13,947
No. Bro, I… We have to stop.

489
00:26:15,323 --> 00:26:16,783
You have to stop.

490
00:26:20,203 --> 00:26:22,289
You're digging way too much for me.

491
00:26:25,917 --> 00:26:30,922
I was running pretty hard,
partying and drinking, and the drug stuff.

492
00:26:31,006 --> 00:26:33,216
I was completely done after that.

493
00:26:36,344 --> 00:26:40,599
You know, the problem with me at the time
was that "Hulk Hogan" was just a business.

494
00:26:40,682 --> 00:26:46,521
I just didn't realize the responsibility
that came along with it,

495
00:26:46,605 --> 00:26:48,815
as Hulk Hogan, the role model.

496
00:26:48,898 --> 00:26:50,734
Yeah.

497
00:26:52,277 --> 00:26:54,821
Excuse me, I'm gonna step right here.

498
00:26:54,904 --> 00:26:57,949
Any questions or anything anybody
would like to ask? How about it?

499
00:26:58,033 --> 00:26:59,409
Would you show your muscles?

500
00:26:59,492 --> 00:27:01,828
-You guys wanna see my muscles?
-Yeah!

501
00:27:05,165 --> 00:27:07,792
When I saw the respect
the fans had for Hulk Hogan,

502
00:27:07,876 --> 00:27:10,295
I quit being cynical about it, you know.

503
00:27:10,378 --> 00:27:12,464
I started thinking,
"Wow, this is really cool."

504
00:27:12,547 --> 00:27:15,425
Before, it was all "work,"
and it really didn't matter.

505
00:27:15,508 --> 00:27:19,387
But it really did matter
what the people thought, you know.

506
00:27:19,471 --> 00:27:21,973
I wanted to be closer
to who the character was.

507
00:27:22,057 --> 00:27:26,394
Your 8th International
Summer Special Olympic Games.

508
00:27:27,437 --> 00:27:30,982
I never really prepared for it.
It just started happening.

509
00:27:31,066 --> 00:27:33,735
The Make-A-Wish kids started showing up.
They wanted to meet me.

510
00:27:36,488 --> 00:27:40,867
Instead of seeing Mr. T or Mickey Mouse,
they wanted to come see me.

511
00:27:40,950 --> 00:27:43,244
I started seeing one at a time,
then two at a time.

512
00:27:43,328 --> 00:27:45,747
Sometimes it was five or six,
ten at a time.

513
00:27:45,830 --> 00:27:47,540
Here at Madison Square Garden,

514
00:27:47,624 --> 00:27:49,959
there are well over
18,000 special children.

515
00:27:50,043 --> 00:27:52,337
-Do you know who Hulk Hogan is?
-Yeah.

516
00:27:52,420 --> 00:27:54,464
Yeah, he's gonna be here today.

517
00:27:54,547 --> 00:27:56,508
-He is?
-Hulk Hogan's gonna be here.

518
00:27:56,591 --> 00:28:00,345
They're survivors, hanging in.
All happy with smiles on their faces.

519
00:28:00,428 --> 00:28:01,846
And it hurts a little bit.

520
00:28:01,930 --> 00:28:04,766
I wish I could give these kids
what I have, a healthy body.

521
00:28:04,849 --> 00:28:10,313
It gave them something to believe in,
an "I, too, can live like a Hulkamaniac."

522
00:28:10,397 --> 00:28:12,982
-Hey, big guy. How you doing?
-Fine.

523
00:28:13,066 --> 00:28:16,069
Oh, boy. You look like
a Hulkamaniac to me.

524
00:28:16,152 --> 00:28:18,279
He was amazing
with the Make-the-Wish kids.

525
00:28:18,363 --> 00:28:20,615
He would always put them first.

526
00:28:20,699 --> 00:28:24,244
I'm glad to meet you. Don't break my arm.
I gotta go to work in a little while.

527
00:28:24,327 --> 00:28:26,913
-All right.
-I'm glad to meet you.

528
00:28:26,996 --> 00:28:28,039
I'm worried.

529
00:28:28,123 --> 00:28:30,375
-Worried about what?
-Well, tomorrow.

530
00:28:30,959 --> 00:28:33,503
-Oh, yeah.
-What do you think I ought to do?

531
00:28:33,586 --> 00:28:35,964
Well, I don't know.

532
00:28:36,047 --> 00:28:38,007
Just do your best.

533
00:28:38,091 --> 00:28:39,759
That's good advice, isn't it?

534
00:28:40,343 --> 00:28:44,889
To have these kids as fans
is such a huge responsibility.

535
00:28:45,557 --> 00:28:48,059
Hulk Hogan was able
to capture their imagination.

536
00:28:48,143 --> 00:28:49,853
Whether it was the size…

537
00:28:49,936 --> 00:28:51,730
God bless you, all right?

538
00:28:51,813 --> 00:28:55,942
I love you. Don't get in any trouble,
or I'll have to come and body slam you.

539
00:28:56,025 --> 00:29:00,238
…or the fact that he was able to be booked
against these big monsters and overcome.

540
00:29:00,321 --> 00:29:02,532
-What's up, big man?
-Hey.

541
00:29:02,615 --> 00:29:03,700
Everything good?

542
00:29:03,783 --> 00:29:06,703
When I was six years old,
my dad took us to WrestleMania III.

543
00:29:06,786 --> 00:29:10,582
I was like, "Oh my God!"
I remember that day. I was a little kid.

544
00:29:10,665 --> 00:29:12,125
WrestleMania III

545
00:29:12,208 --> 00:29:17,422
meant something very different
in the evolution of Hulkamania.

546
00:29:17,505 --> 00:29:20,592
WrestleMania III will be your last lesson.

547
00:29:21,176 --> 00:29:22,844
Talk about heroes.

548
00:29:22,927 --> 00:29:26,973
I'd looked up to André,
you know… my whole life.

549
00:29:27,056 --> 00:29:28,892
Oh! Oh!

550
00:29:28,975 --> 00:29:30,268
He was my mentor.

551
00:29:30,351 --> 00:29:33,646
I'm really proud of you,
and you are a good wrestler.

552
00:29:33,730 --> 00:29:36,524
You're the reason
I got into professional wrestling.

553
00:29:36,608 --> 00:29:38,401
You were like a god to me, a role model!

554
00:29:39,068 --> 00:29:43,448
And wrestling fans had been waiting
to see me fight him for the belt.

555
00:29:44,616 --> 00:29:46,409
What are you doing, man?

556
00:29:46,493 --> 00:29:48,119
You can't leave like this, man.

557
00:29:48,203 --> 00:29:49,788
Used to respect the guy a lot.

558
00:29:49,871 --> 00:29:54,125
André was viewed
as someone who couldn't be beaten.

559
00:29:54,751 --> 00:29:57,504
He was called
the eighth wonder of the world.

560
00:29:57,587 --> 00:30:00,507
The most
extraordinary athlete of all time.

561
00:30:00,590 --> 00:30:03,760
They weighed him at the Detroit airport
on the baggage scale,

562
00:30:03,843 --> 00:30:05,970
he was like 600 pounds or something crazy.

563
00:30:06,054 --> 00:30:09,098
In later years,
every time Hulk told the story,

564
00:30:09,182 --> 00:30:11,226
André gained 100 pounds.

565
00:30:11,309 --> 00:30:12,727
For those who believe,

566
00:30:12,811 --> 00:30:17,148
it's like when St. Paul had his epiphany
on the road to Damascus.

567
00:30:17,232 --> 00:30:18,775
The whole earth is gonna shake!

568
00:30:18,858 --> 00:30:21,361
When Jesus rose from the dead.

569
00:30:21,444 --> 00:30:24,781
What are they gonna think
when the giant hits the ground?

570
00:30:25,365 --> 00:30:28,284
This is the main event of the evening.

571
00:30:29,494 --> 00:30:33,039
The people,
they were right there with all of it.

572
00:30:33,122 --> 00:30:36,042
He ripped the shirt
off the champion as well as the crucifix.

573
00:30:36,125 --> 00:30:37,335
Seven-foot-five.

574
00:30:37,418 --> 00:30:41,214
First time I've been in the ring
not knowing what was gonna happen.

575
00:30:41,297 --> 00:30:43,299
Look at the size of the giant.

576
00:30:43,383 --> 00:30:44,968
What's Hogan saying to him?

577
00:30:45,051 --> 00:30:46,719
What could Hogan
possibly be saying to him?

578
00:30:47,303 --> 00:30:48,847
"I love you to death, brother."

579
00:30:48,930 --> 00:30:52,308
"Thank you so much, man,
for helping me out all these years."

580
00:30:52,392 --> 00:30:54,310
That was the conversation.

581
00:30:54,394 --> 00:30:56,271
And he looked pissed.

582
00:30:56,354 --> 00:31:01,067
He looked like a rabid great white shark
that was gonna tear me apart.

583
00:31:02,944 --> 00:31:06,281
Big right hand blocked by the champion.

584
00:31:06,364 --> 00:31:09,784
And the Hulkster unloading,
going for a slam. He almost got him.

585
00:31:09,868 --> 00:31:14,747
The storyline is
no one had body slammed André the Giant.

586
00:31:14,831 --> 00:31:17,083
With ease! That's right!

587
00:31:17,166 --> 00:31:18,585
It's impossible.

588
00:31:18,668 --> 00:31:21,713
André telling the champion,
"Get up, get up."

589
00:31:21,796 --> 00:31:24,632
I said, "Well, I'm dead
because you're gonna kill me."

590
00:31:24,716 --> 00:31:28,177
Oh, the bear hug!
We could get a submission on this.

591
00:31:31,306 --> 00:31:35,226
He's facing a man
who has never been beaten in 15 years.

592
00:31:36,102 --> 00:31:37,937
He's taking the air away from Hogan.

593
00:31:38,021 --> 00:31:41,524
Hogan is not being allowed
to get a full breath of oxygen in there.

594
00:31:41,608 --> 00:31:45,695
When you talk about who's the greatest,
the greatest is, was, or ever will be,

595
00:31:45,778 --> 00:31:47,488
or greatest in the world,

596
00:31:48,489 --> 00:31:50,825
I challenge anybody in this business…

597
00:31:50,909 --> 00:31:53,036
The referee checking the arm. Look.

598
00:31:53,119 --> 00:31:55,079
…to do one move better than mine.

599
00:31:55,163 --> 00:31:57,707
One more time.
If that arm drops, it's over.

600
00:31:57,790 --> 00:32:01,044
Which, as etched in time,
would be a piece of history.

601
00:32:01,127 --> 00:32:04,923
Do whatever sidekick you want to do,
whatever suplex you want to do,

602
00:32:05,006 --> 00:32:07,634
whatever twirly twisty thing
off the top rope.

603
00:32:07,717 --> 00:32:09,719
What I did will live forever.

604
00:32:09,802 --> 00:32:11,846
Oh, look at that. It's up there.

605
00:32:11,930 --> 00:32:14,223
Listen to these fans.

606
00:32:18,061 --> 00:32:21,439
Right on the side of the ear.
And another one, and another one!

607
00:32:22,106 --> 00:32:24,901
-He dropped him!
-He dropped the big guy!

608
00:32:24,984 --> 00:32:26,569
He's Hulking up.

609
00:32:26,653 --> 00:32:29,113
That adrenaline can do wonders.

610
00:32:29,197 --> 00:32:31,950
We're seeing
what this guy is really made of.

611
00:32:32,033 --> 00:32:33,117
What he is.

612
00:32:33,201 --> 00:32:35,828
The greatest professional athlete
in the world today.

613
00:32:35,912 --> 00:32:36,913
Look at this!

614
00:32:36,996 --> 00:32:39,499
-He slammed him!
-He's out!

615
00:32:39,582 --> 00:32:41,125
I don't believe it!

616
00:32:41,834 --> 00:32:44,587
-I don't believe it!
-Hulk dropping a big one!

617
00:32:45,338 --> 00:32:46,714
Over from the jumper.

618
00:32:46,798 --> 00:32:48,132
It's over!

619
00:32:49,550 --> 00:32:52,220
-Unbelievable!
-It's all over!

620
00:32:54,389 --> 00:32:55,974
After that, I told him,

621
00:32:56,057 --> 00:32:59,018
"You're never gonna be
Terry Bollea again, Hulk."

622
00:32:59,102 --> 00:33:01,938
"When you walk out there
with that headband on,

623
00:33:02,605 --> 00:33:06,234
it's not Terry Bollea, it's Hulk Hogan.
And that's the way the people see you."

624
00:33:07,068 --> 00:33:09,445
He became the legend, the myth.

625
00:33:10,196 --> 00:33:11,656
Hulk Hogan, the immortal one.

626
00:33:11,739 --> 00:33:15,326
He's thanking
the guy upstairs, Jess. As he always does.

627
00:33:15,410 --> 00:33:20,456
The power of Hulkamania
made us push everything else aside

628
00:33:20,540 --> 00:33:23,209
and escape into this marvelous movie.

629
00:33:24,627 --> 00:33:27,380
Hulk Hogan turned out to be more real

630
00:33:27,463 --> 00:33:30,550
than any… anyone ever
thought it would be.

631
00:33:30,633 --> 00:33:33,970
It turned out to be who I really am.

632
00:33:35,513 --> 00:33:36,597
Here you go.

633
00:33:38,599 --> 00:33:40,143
Whoa.

634
00:33:41,436 --> 00:33:44,355
I was hoping
these had André's blood on them.

635
00:33:44,439 --> 00:33:46,858
I used to order 12 pair at a time.

636
00:33:46,941 --> 00:33:49,235
Every time I'd order 12 pair, I'd swear,

637
00:33:49,318 --> 00:33:51,029
"Once I'm done
with these 12 pair of boots,

638
00:33:51,112 --> 00:33:53,573
I'm quitting. I'll never wrestle again."

639
00:33:53,656 --> 00:33:56,367
Then I'd order 12 more. Then 12 more.

640
00:33:56,451 --> 00:33:57,660
Then 12 more.

641
00:33:58,286 --> 00:34:02,707
WrestleMania III etched in stone
that I wasn't going anywhere.

642
00:34:04,917 --> 00:34:09,422
I was 700 feet tall in the public's eyes.

643
00:34:11,007 --> 00:34:12,300
Whoo!

644
00:34:12,383 --> 00:34:17,096
There was no corner in the earth
where they didn't know about Hulk Hogan

645
00:34:17,180 --> 00:34:19,307
or what was going on with me.

646
00:34:19,891 --> 00:34:23,394
It was like John Lennon
and Paul McCartney at their heyday.

647
00:34:23,478 --> 00:34:25,605
The people just come out of the woodwork.

648
00:34:25,688 --> 00:34:28,566
It was a who's who
of who would show up at these matches

649
00:34:28,649 --> 00:34:30,568
to meet and talk with me.

650
00:34:30,651 --> 00:34:33,654
Unreal,
Donald Trump, one of the Hulkamaniacs.

651
00:34:33,738 --> 00:34:37,033
There he is right there.
A Hulkamaniac, you really think so?

652
00:34:37,116 --> 00:34:38,326
Absolutely.

653
00:34:38,409 --> 00:34:40,286
It's an honor.
I'll tell you what, it's an honor.

654
00:34:40,369 --> 00:34:42,121
Everybody in the country
wanted this event.

655
00:34:42,205 --> 00:34:43,414
Get on up here.

656
00:34:43,498 --> 00:34:44,957
Come on. Do you believe this?

657
00:34:45,041 --> 00:34:46,250
I'm 6'2".

658
00:34:46,334 --> 00:34:48,586
I want the world to know that I'm 6'2".

659
00:34:48,669 --> 00:34:49,879
And look what I look like.

660
00:34:49,962 --> 00:34:52,173
It was just amazing
to watch this guy work.

661
00:34:52,256 --> 00:34:53,508
I'd heard a lot about him,

662
00:34:53,591 --> 00:34:57,095
but this was the first time
I ever saw him in action in person.

663
00:34:59,388 --> 00:35:02,725
-Nice to see you.
-Sit right in here.

664
00:35:05,478 --> 00:35:06,938
So you go ahead, if you're ready.

665
00:35:07,605 --> 00:35:10,691
I have a big Russia meeting going on, so…

666
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:15,488
Somehow, I became friendly
with Hulk over there, the Hulkster.

667
00:35:15,571 --> 00:35:17,657
He's a good man. He's just a nice guy.

668
00:35:17,740 --> 00:35:20,660
He asked, "Would you do this interview?"
I said, "Why not?"

669
00:35:20,743 --> 00:35:22,370
Here we are in the White House, right?

670
00:35:22,453 --> 00:35:25,414
Get ready, ladies and gentlemen,
for WrestleMania IV,

671
00:35:25,498 --> 00:35:29,961
which will be held
at the Trump Plaza Hotel and Casino.

672
00:35:30,044 --> 00:35:34,048
'88, WrestleMania at Trump Plaza
in Atlantic City.

673
00:35:34,132 --> 00:35:36,342
Oh, there he is, Donald Trump.

674
00:35:36,926 --> 00:35:39,220
Yeah, he's my main man.
He's sitting in my box.

675
00:35:39,303 --> 00:35:42,265
Yeah, he was in there
wrestling his heart out.

676
00:35:42,348 --> 00:35:44,934
Hulk Hogan miraculously on his feet!

677
00:35:45,518 --> 00:35:47,353
Obviously, you need the physical ability.

678
00:35:47,436 --> 00:35:50,648
If he walked in and he was not,
didn't look like that,

679
00:35:50,731 --> 00:35:53,151
I don't care how good an actor you are,
it's not going to work.

680
00:35:53,234 --> 00:35:56,237
Thank God Donald Trump's a Hulkamaniac!

681
00:35:56,320 --> 00:35:59,657
But he's also a showman.
And that would be a good word for him.

682
00:35:59,740 --> 00:36:02,451
Thank you, Hulk Hogan!
Let's get back to action.

683
00:36:02,535 --> 00:36:06,289
I've seen him numerous times.
I've watched him wrestle numerous times.

684
00:36:06,372 --> 00:36:09,959
Trump Plaza is dedicated
to getting the greatest sporting events.

685
00:36:10,042 --> 00:36:12,753
We're really delighted
to land WrestleMania V.

686
00:36:12,837 --> 00:36:15,631
But we… we sort of had
a good relationship early on.

687
00:36:15,715 --> 00:36:16,924
It was a good chemistry.

688
00:36:17,008 --> 00:36:20,136
-Trump. How you doing?
-The big man. Come here.

689
00:36:20,219 --> 00:36:21,554
Come in and shut the door.

690
00:36:21,637 --> 00:36:24,390
-How are the kids?
-They're great. They send their regards.

691
00:36:24,473 --> 00:36:25,641
They gonna be ringside?

692
00:36:25,725 --> 00:36:28,769
He's just a big, strong guy
who's got a good heart.

693
00:36:28,853 --> 00:36:30,271
He's a very loyal person.

694
00:36:30,354 --> 00:36:32,732
If you want to be in Hulk's corner,
that's all right.

695
00:36:32,815 --> 00:36:35,276
-I'll take care of you outside the ring.
-Sounds good.

696
00:36:35,359 --> 00:36:37,570
Yes. I'll take care of everyone.

697
00:36:37,653 --> 00:36:38,529
Hogan!

698
00:36:38,613 --> 00:36:43,201
Wrestling is a mimicking of life.
There's a winner and a loser.

699
00:36:43,284 --> 00:36:44,285
Here we go.

700
00:36:44,368 --> 00:36:47,997
-Hulk was at the top of the game.
-Hulkster's out of there!

701
00:36:48,080 --> 00:36:49,540
You'll think he was beat…

702
00:36:49,624 --> 00:36:52,043
Nobody's ever come back from that elbow!

703
00:36:52,126 --> 00:36:54,295
…and then you'll see the finger moving.

704
00:36:56,923 --> 00:36:59,884
The finger going like this,
and all of a sudden--

705
00:36:59,967 --> 00:37:02,470
Can you show me? What does he do?

706
00:37:02,553 --> 00:37:05,264
No, I've given you enough there.

707
00:37:06,974 --> 00:37:11,687
And a leg-drop! One, two! Yeah!

708
00:37:15,149 --> 00:37:18,611
Business-wise,
his work ethic rubbed off on me.

709
00:37:18,694 --> 00:37:21,614
How he recreated
the whole New York skyline.

710
00:37:22,490 --> 00:37:25,409
Hulk has a great brand.
He's had a lot of success.

711
00:37:25,493 --> 00:37:26,994
Yeah!

712
00:37:27,078 --> 00:37:30,581
He was the biggest ever
in this world of wrestling.

713
00:37:31,666 --> 00:37:33,542
And it's a pretty big world.

714
00:37:39,966 --> 00:37:43,511
He was the first one
that had merchandising.

715
00:37:43,594 --> 00:37:45,096
Hulk was great that way.

716
00:37:45,680 --> 00:37:47,390
That's Hulk Hogan!

717
00:37:47,473 --> 00:37:49,976
Wrestling buddies are looking for action.

718
00:37:50,059 --> 00:37:52,770
The amount of money
that is made off a product…

719
00:37:52,853 --> 00:37:54,272
Dropkick!

720
00:37:54,355 --> 00:37:55,898
…that's where it's all at.

721
00:37:55,982 --> 00:37:58,401
Not by putting asses in seats.

722
00:37:58,484 --> 00:38:00,528
The marketing of professional wrestling

723
00:38:00,611 --> 00:38:02,571
has turned
into a multi-million dollar business.

724
00:38:02,655 --> 00:38:04,323
Hulkster rules, brother!

725
00:38:05,574 --> 00:38:08,661
When I say, you know, Hulk Hogan
was the greatest wrestler in the world,

726
00:38:08,744 --> 00:38:11,914
it's because I was the guy
who generates the most revenue.

727
00:38:11,998 --> 00:38:13,708
You need to be able to walk in a room

728
00:38:13,791 --> 00:38:16,836
where you're talking
to 4,000 buyers from Walmart.

729
00:38:16,919 --> 00:38:20,965
I'm so thrilled, so happy about the new
Hulk Hogan rock wrestling cartoon.

730
00:38:21,048 --> 00:38:23,968
There's a lot of responsibility
with being a businessman

731
00:38:24,051 --> 00:38:26,846
outside the "normal" wrestler
that was driving down the ring,

732
00:38:26,929 --> 00:38:29,223
chugging some beers before the match.

733
00:38:29,724 --> 00:38:33,602
You need to know merchandise,
licensing, ancillary, talk their language.

734
00:38:33,686 --> 00:38:35,354
Hogan's the only number one.

735
00:38:35,980 --> 00:38:37,982
There is no one better.

736
00:38:38,065 --> 00:38:42,778
You also need to be able to hold your own
with 30 women, be able to relate to them.

737
00:38:42,862 --> 00:38:44,238
Hulk Hogan is sexy.

738
00:38:44,322 --> 00:38:46,782
-He's a wonder.
-Good build, good body.

739
00:38:46,866 --> 00:38:48,701
Best looking wrestler in the business.

740
00:38:48,784 --> 00:38:50,036
Good for the kids!

741
00:38:50,119 --> 00:38:52,621
I'm approving ten or 15
new products every week.

742
00:38:52,705 --> 00:38:57,209
Underwear, bedsheets, potty seats for kids
to learn how to go to the bathroom.

743
00:38:57,293 --> 00:38:58,836
16-inch high.

744
00:38:58,919 --> 00:39:01,005
A Hulk Hogan vibrating action figure.

745
00:39:01,088 --> 00:39:04,008
And that… that had
to get knocked off right away.

746
00:39:04,091 --> 00:39:07,178
-Why is that?
-I have no idea.

747
00:39:07,887 --> 00:39:11,724
Hulk Hogan turned
into a licensing merchandising monster.

748
00:39:17,980 --> 00:39:21,692
There's Hulk.
It's a beautiful day on the beach here.

749
00:39:21,776 --> 00:39:24,653
Strange in those clothes,
I'm not used to seeing him all dressed up.

750
00:39:25,863 --> 00:39:28,699
His career became all-consuming.

751
00:39:29,408 --> 00:39:33,371
He would have a promo,
a commercial, a photo shoot.

752
00:39:33,871 --> 00:39:38,125
Then he had a wrestling match at night.
He would live, sleep, eat, and breathe it.

753
00:39:38,209 --> 00:39:41,212
The 900 number might be
the quickest and easiest thing.

754
00:39:41,295 --> 00:39:43,923
I got to a point where I was like,
"You know something, Terry?"

755
00:39:45,174 --> 00:39:47,802
"Ever since we got married,
we've just been on the run."

756
00:39:47,885 --> 00:39:52,264
Like Bonnie and Clyde, you know,
it's never been a situated situation.

757
00:39:52,348 --> 00:39:55,142
And I'm like,
"I need a situated situation right now."

758
00:39:56,310 --> 00:39:59,355
"And I think maybe it'd be
a good time now if we had a kid."

759
00:39:59,438 --> 00:40:00,940
I want to have a baby.

760
00:40:03,818 --> 00:40:05,569
Nine months later, Brooke came.

761
00:40:09,990 --> 00:40:13,202
This big man's holding this little baby
in a pink blanket.

762
00:40:13,285 --> 00:40:16,455
I mean, it was like, he couldn't believe
that he had a baby.

763
00:40:21,669 --> 00:40:23,671
Oh no, ice-cold water on Daddy.

764
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:28,426
My whole reason for living
changed instantly.

765
00:40:28,509 --> 00:40:30,886
Come on, give Dad a kiss.

766
00:40:33,931 --> 00:40:37,226
No! Daddy!

767
00:40:37,309 --> 00:40:41,063
He became more of a family man,
and he liked doing family things.

768
00:40:41,647 --> 00:40:44,567
I had no idea my whole focus would change

769
00:40:44,650 --> 00:40:47,403
to try to protect this human being.

770
00:40:47,486 --> 00:40:53,951
And what to my wandering eyes
should appear but a huge Hulkamania.

771
00:40:55,286 --> 00:40:59,707
Lindoochay, what do you have
to say for yourself on this sunny day?

772
00:41:01,417 --> 00:41:04,795
We already did that.
That's why we're in this predicament.

773
00:41:04,879 --> 00:41:08,507
Ba-boom. Holy shit.
Let me get back, my lenses are fogged up.

774
00:41:08,591 --> 00:41:12,219
At the time, Nini, Linda's grandmother,
was living with us.

775
00:41:12,303 --> 00:41:14,054
I came downstairs for coffee.

776
00:41:14,138 --> 00:41:18,434
She goes, "I want to let you know,
congratulations, Linda's pregnant."

777
00:41:19,643 --> 00:41:20,769
I went, "What?"

778
00:41:20,853 --> 00:41:23,105
Thanks, Nini, with your big mouth.

779
00:41:23,189 --> 00:41:24,815
I said, "How'd you get pregnant?"

780
00:41:24,899 --> 00:41:28,360
She goes, "I quit taking birth control.
I decided not to tell you." I went…

781
00:41:30,613 --> 00:41:31,447
Cool.

782
00:41:31,530 --> 00:41:34,116
That's okay. He got over it.

783
00:41:34,867 --> 00:41:38,621
My son Nick came along,
and I had a baby boy. I was ecstatic.

784
00:41:38,704 --> 00:41:42,041
I'd like to lose some.
My life is in shambles.

785
00:41:42,124 --> 00:41:43,959
-No.
-Shut up.

786
00:41:45,044 --> 00:41:48,547
It was something
that was printed in my brain,

787
00:41:48,631 --> 00:41:51,008
that I didn't want to live
the way I grew up.

788
00:41:51,091 --> 00:41:55,513
Not that my parents didn't love me.
It wasn't a verbal or a physical thing.

789
00:41:56,472 --> 00:41:59,308
There's people I love, man.
I'm not afraid to tell people.

790
00:41:59,391 --> 00:42:03,020
He was always affectionate with the kids.
Never forgot to say "I love you."

791
00:42:03,103 --> 00:42:06,899
Oh, there she goes.
One, two, kicks out. She's up.

792
00:42:06,982 --> 00:42:08,776
She's staring me down.

793
00:42:08,859 --> 00:42:11,028
I thought you were a fighter,
I'm supposed to punch you.

794
00:42:11,111 --> 00:42:12,947
You're on my side?

795
00:42:13,030 --> 00:42:14,073
Aah!

796
00:42:14,156 --> 00:42:15,533
Let them hang.

797
00:42:15,616 --> 00:42:17,201
Yes, sir, buddy.

798
00:42:18,327 --> 00:42:20,204
That's that come to Jesus set.
There you go.

799
00:42:22,873 --> 00:42:23,916
We're not done.

800
00:42:23,999 --> 00:42:25,584
Whoo-ee!

801
00:42:25,668 --> 00:42:27,461
Stick with it. Good.

802
00:42:30,214 --> 00:42:33,467
The person that's been around the longest
and has stuck with me through everything

803
00:42:33,551 --> 00:42:34,426
is my son, Nick.

804
00:42:34,510 --> 00:42:37,805
That breeze coming off the ocean.
Oh my God, that feels good.

805
00:42:38,639 --> 00:42:39,640
Oh, man.

806
00:42:39,723 --> 00:42:41,517
When Nick is around, I hang like this.

807
00:42:41,600 --> 00:42:42,685
You guys see me do that?

808
00:42:42,768 --> 00:42:44,645
It's hard to walk straight.
I'm off balance.

809
00:42:45,604 --> 00:42:47,856
You know, it's kind of embarrassing.

810
00:42:47,940 --> 00:42:49,441
Ego-wise, you know.

811
00:42:50,025 --> 00:42:54,405
Dad, you do more weight than I do.
You're still stronger than me.

812
00:42:54,488 --> 00:42:59,034
He was just this, you know,
action figure that was my dad, you know.

813
00:42:59,118 --> 00:43:01,078
So I still see him like that.

814
00:43:01,161 --> 00:43:03,205
I don't remember Hulkamania.

815
00:43:03,956 --> 00:43:05,624
I was so young at the time.

816
00:43:05,708 --> 00:43:09,712
So I never really understood
what Hulk Hogan, what wrestling was,

817
00:43:09,795 --> 00:43:11,755
what any of that really meant.

818
00:43:12,506 --> 00:43:15,676
My friends, they'd come over and be like,
"Am I gonna meet your dad?"

819
00:43:15,759 --> 00:43:16,969
"Is your dad gonna be there?"

820
00:43:18,220 --> 00:43:19,680
The first time I met Hogan

821
00:43:19,763 --> 00:43:22,766
was at one of his birthday parties
that he threw on his yacht.

822
00:43:23,350 --> 00:43:25,978
These girls are gonna have
a good time on this cruise.

823
00:43:26,061 --> 00:43:28,230
My dad was a part
of that very special era.

824
00:43:28,314 --> 00:43:30,149
This is the nasty guy. He's The Anvil.

825
00:43:30,232 --> 00:43:32,818
No, we're… we're not nasty.

826
00:43:32,901 --> 00:43:38,157
Like, I was in awe. Wow.
He just kind of exuded that, like, star.

827
00:43:38,240 --> 00:43:41,076
You see him,
and he's got this presence, this aura.

828
00:43:41,160 --> 00:43:42,453
He was the guy.

829
00:43:43,829 --> 00:43:49,585
I've never met a top person in wrestling
that has had an easy, smooth road.

830
00:43:49,668 --> 00:43:51,170
Woo-hoo!

831
00:43:51,253 --> 00:43:56,884
Even my dad wasn't a top star,
but my dad was gone 300 days a year.

832
00:43:56,967 --> 00:44:00,054
Jim Neidhart, in the ring, hammering down.

833
00:44:00,137 --> 00:44:02,765
I saw my dad more on TV than in real life.

834
00:44:02,848 --> 00:44:04,350
Just like Hogan with his kids.

835
00:44:04,433 --> 00:44:06,268
Tell them, Brooke. Who's here?

836
00:44:07,019 --> 00:44:09,897
Brooke and Nicholas and Daddy.

837
00:44:09,980 --> 00:44:11,649
Yay!

838
00:44:11,732 --> 00:44:14,443
Brooke and Nick had to share him
with everybody else.

839
00:44:14,526 --> 00:44:16,195
I love Hulk Hogan!

840
00:44:16,278 --> 00:44:18,238
There you go, Hulkamania.

841
00:44:19,531 --> 00:44:21,867
They had to share him
with the other boys and girls.

842
00:44:21,950 --> 00:44:23,285
Look at this big one.

843
00:44:24,286 --> 00:44:26,789
He couldn't be a real father
because he was Hulk Hogan.

844
00:44:26,872 --> 00:44:28,082
He was not Terry Bollea.

845
00:44:29,458 --> 00:44:34,922
Trading a real life for a wrestling life,
it's a choice that can destroy a family.

846
00:44:35,005 --> 00:44:36,590
Come here.

847
00:44:36,674 --> 00:44:37,800
Come here.

848
00:44:38,592 --> 00:44:39,718
Hello?

849
00:44:39,802 --> 00:44:41,845
Hi. We're just playing in the kitchen.

850
00:44:45,265 --> 00:44:47,518
Yo, Nick, this is Dad.

851
00:44:47,601 --> 00:44:49,937
Hulk loved his family. He loved his wife.

852
00:44:50,020 --> 00:44:52,690
He'd be on the road,
"I'm just gonna keep my family happy."

853
00:44:52,773 --> 00:44:54,525
"Whatever Linda wants,
that's what we'll do."

854
00:44:54,608 --> 00:44:56,902
Are you done? Okay.

855
00:44:56,985 --> 00:45:01,240
Everything this man did,
you were to have the best life possible.

856
00:45:01,323 --> 00:45:04,451
But what good is a good life
if you don't have your husband with you?

857
00:45:04,535 --> 00:45:06,453
I get to have such a nice Mother's Day.

858
00:45:06,537 --> 00:45:11,667
Terry just sent three dozen
long-stemmed red roses.

859
00:45:11,750 --> 00:45:14,461
He was gone for 12 days
and then only home for two sometimes.

860
00:45:14,545 --> 00:45:17,589
Hey, Brooke, come over here.
No, turn, turn, turn.

861
00:45:17,673 --> 00:45:19,133
Then, boom, we're gone again.

862
00:45:19,216 --> 00:45:21,135
Leaving for England. I don't want him to.

863
00:45:21,218 --> 00:45:22,052
I don't either.

864
00:45:22,136 --> 00:45:25,556
My kids were starting to freak out
when I'd leave.

865
00:45:25,639 --> 00:45:27,099
-Crying.
-Oh no.

866
00:45:27,182 --> 00:45:29,184
Come on. Why were you crying now?

867
00:45:29,268 --> 00:45:31,603
It took him a long time
to get out the front door.

868
00:45:31,687 --> 00:45:33,105
And it probably affected him

869
00:45:33,188 --> 00:45:35,315
until he finally got, you know,

870
00:45:35,399 --> 00:45:37,443
vodka and tonic
on the plane and got going.

871
00:45:37,526 --> 00:45:40,654
But, honestly, I know
it must have been hard for him.

872
00:45:40,738 --> 00:45:42,030
Oh, my gosh.

873
00:45:42,865 --> 00:45:44,575
Ugh. It was killing me.

874
00:45:44,658 --> 00:45:48,829
And I told Linda
that I'm gonna gracefully approach Vince

875
00:45:48,912 --> 00:45:51,457
and start winding this down
to a part-time schedule.

876
00:45:51,540 --> 00:45:53,375
It made it really hard for him.

877
00:45:53,459 --> 00:45:55,335
We didn't have anybody else at that time

878
00:45:55,419 --> 00:45:57,880
that could draw the thousands
and thousands of people.

879
00:45:57,963 --> 00:46:00,466
You have to give them what they want.
And it was just me.

880
00:46:00,549 --> 00:46:05,763
As he's opening his book, and he goes,
"Okay, how am I gonna book Cincinnati?"

881
00:46:05,846 --> 00:46:07,264
"How am I gonna book Boston?"

882
00:46:07,347 --> 00:46:11,059
"How am I gonna book New York
when I can't put your name on the book?"

883
00:46:11,143 --> 00:46:12,770
"How am I gonna do this, Terry?"

884
00:46:14,396 --> 00:46:16,732
I said, "Well, we need another star."

885
00:46:20,861 --> 00:46:22,821
The Ultimate Warrior came along.

886
00:46:22,905 --> 00:46:27,117
Warrior had a look.
Warrior had ungodly charisma.

887
00:46:27,618 --> 00:46:30,329
Ultimate Warrior was just custom-made.

888
00:46:30,412 --> 00:46:34,875
Something that guys would want to be,
and something girls would want to be with.

889
00:46:34,958 --> 00:46:38,754
He has this belligerent body.
He has the face paint.

890
00:46:38,837 --> 00:46:41,632
And Vince has put
all the neon colors on him.

891
00:46:41,715 --> 00:46:43,842
Much brighter than the red and yellow.

892
00:46:44,843 --> 00:46:47,888
I was someone
who bought into the Ultimate Warrior.

893
00:46:47,971 --> 00:46:50,098
I really liked the Ultimate Warrior.

894
00:46:50,182 --> 00:46:52,768
I was so excited.
And you could feel that energy.

895
00:46:52,851 --> 00:46:59,233
Now, Hulk Hogan,
I come to take what you believe in

896
00:46:59,316 --> 00:47:01,652
further than you ever could!

897
00:47:01,735 --> 00:47:05,781
The building blocks all made sense.

898
00:47:06,573 --> 00:47:09,993
If it worked for Hulk Hogan,
why can't you do it for him?

899
00:47:10,577 --> 00:47:14,122
I am the chosen one.

900
00:47:14,832 --> 00:47:19,044
And Vince goes, "I'm gonna give
the Ultimate Warrior a big push."

901
00:47:19,127 --> 00:47:23,549
Something's going to happen, Warriors.

902
00:47:23,632 --> 00:47:27,261
I can feel it!

903
00:47:27,344 --> 00:47:29,638
Turned out to be
probably one of the worst ideas

904
00:47:29,721 --> 00:47:31,849
in the history of professional wrestling.

905
00:47:32,599 --> 00:47:36,311
The Ultimate Shit. You got to know
what the hell you're doing.

906
00:47:37,729 --> 00:47:39,898
Remember what's going on in the ring.

907
00:47:39,982 --> 00:47:41,984
What was supposed to happen, more or less,

908
00:47:42,067 --> 00:47:45,362
was sort of a changing of the guard.
Ultimate Warrior was supposed

909
00:47:45,445 --> 00:47:48,657
to lead the company and the brand
into the next century.

910
00:47:51,285 --> 00:47:55,789
What no one
really seemed to stop and consider

911
00:47:55,873 --> 00:47:59,209
is what do we do with this guy
after he wins?

912
00:47:59,293 --> 00:48:01,336
When you step in the Sky Dome,

913
00:48:01,420 --> 00:48:05,424
when you feel the energy
that'll run wild throughout the arena,

914
00:48:05,507 --> 00:48:06,758
those are my people.

915
00:48:06,842 --> 00:48:08,427
That's my energy, brother.

916
00:48:08,510 --> 00:48:12,806
The muscles on my skeleton
are of a different texture.

917
00:48:12,890 --> 00:48:13,765
Do it again.

918
00:48:13,849 --> 00:48:16,268
He doesn't have the walk,
he doesn't have the talk.

919
00:48:16,351 --> 00:48:19,730
When you send him out to Toys "R" Us
or to a convention…

920
00:48:19,813 --> 00:48:21,607
He was deader than Kelsey's nuts.

921
00:48:21,690 --> 00:48:23,775
-Can you look up for a second?
-Yes. There you go.

922
00:48:23,859 --> 00:48:24,693
Thank you.

923
00:48:24,776 --> 00:48:27,154
All the freaks are out today.

924
00:48:27,237 --> 00:48:30,908
I remember thinking,
"Warrior's not the guy."

925
00:48:30,991 --> 00:48:33,744
-"Warrior's not gonna carry it."
-He had nothing on the bone.

926
00:48:33,827 --> 00:48:36,038
For the life… Oh, fuck.

927
00:48:36,955 --> 00:48:40,584
The Ultimate Warrior
was not well-liked at all.

928
00:48:40,667 --> 00:48:42,836
Fuck. Go again.

929
00:48:42,920 --> 00:48:45,631
He knew everything. He didn't give a shit.

930
00:48:46,840 --> 00:48:49,426
"Listen to me,"
is basically what he'd tell you.

931
00:48:50,427 --> 00:48:53,055
And if you don't like it,
shut the fuck up.

932
00:48:53,138 --> 00:48:56,558
If anything, we were kind of
clinging to Hulk going, "You're the guy."

933
00:48:56,642 --> 00:48:59,394
You know, it also seems
as though you've been chosen, man.

934
00:48:59,478 --> 00:49:02,814
Just like I was,
to lead the masses to higher ground.

935
00:49:04,775 --> 00:49:05,609
Wow.

936
00:49:07,486 --> 00:49:11,531
It was decided, "Okay, well,
put the title on the Ultimate Warrior

937
00:49:11,615 --> 00:49:15,953
and let Hulk endorse him
and see what he can do."

938
00:49:16,036 --> 00:49:18,622
What a match-up this is going to be!

939
00:49:18,705 --> 00:49:23,168
This is what has brought 68,000 strong
here to the Sky Dome!

940
00:49:23,251 --> 00:49:24,920
Look at the intensity!

941
00:49:25,921 --> 00:49:28,966
Hulk was like, "I'll put him over
just the way you want."

942
00:49:29,633 --> 00:49:31,009
"And he'll be your new star."

943
00:49:31,093 --> 00:49:34,304
If you put someone over,
that means you're letting them win.

944
00:49:34,388 --> 00:49:38,058
And actually putting them over means
making them look good in the match too.

945
00:49:38,141 --> 00:49:41,478
He… He couldn't wrestle. He was horrible.

946
00:49:42,187 --> 00:49:46,108
Unless he had somebody
actually leading him step-by-step,

947
00:49:46,191 --> 00:49:47,693
you know, he was horrible.

948
00:49:49,277 --> 00:49:52,364
Probably about three-minute mark,
he wanted to end the match.

949
00:49:52,447 --> 00:49:55,283
"Let's go home."
I said, "No, we're not going home."

950
00:49:55,784 --> 00:49:57,285
I said, "No, bro."

951
00:49:57,369 --> 00:50:01,707
-This is a winner here.
-If you're gonna beat me, earn it.

952
00:50:01,790 --> 00:50:06,253
Walked him around the ring for another
15, 20 minutes, maybe 15 minutes.

953
00:50:06,336 --> 00:50:08,422
That had to be like pulling damn teeth.

954
00:50:08,505 --> 00:50:11,425
-He's going for a slam!
-I don't believe it!

955
00:50:11,508 --> 00:50:13,093
He got him up!

956
00:50:13,176 --> 00:50:15,846
He was totally out of gas.
He couldn't walk or breathe.

957
00:50:17,180 --> 00:50:21,351
Look out, the big splash!
One, two, and it's over!

958
00:50:21,435 --> 00:50:27,858
Rather than letting
the Ultimate Warrior exalt in his triumph,

959
00:50:27,941 --> 00:50:32,612
Hulk Hogan pondered the belt,
and he shook his head.

960
00:50:32,696 --> 00:50:35,490
It felt like the story was Hogan losing.

961
00:50:35,574 --> 00:50:37,409
And I, even at a young age, thought,

962
00:50:37,492 --> 00:50:41,121
"How cool do you have to be
that it's still your story?"

963
00:50:41,204 --> 00:50:45,459
You losing is more of the tale
than someone new being anointed.

964
00:50:46,209 --> 00:50:52,049
Answering to the power
of the Ultimate Warrior.

965
00:50:52,632 --> 00:50:55,927
I think a lot of people resented
the Ultimate Warrior as champion,

966
00:50:56,011 --> 00:50:57,596
and the audience…

967
00:50:58,722 --> 00:51:00,474
I don't wanna say they saw through it,

968
00:51:00,557 --> 00:51:02,476
but the audience said
he was no Hulk Hogan.

969
00:51:04,936 --> 00:51:07,355
The Ultimate Warrior didn't work out.

970
00:51:07,439 --> 00:51:10,025
He was immediately shut down.

971
00:51:10,108 --> 00:51:13,737
New World Wrestling
Entertainment Champion!

972
00:51:13,820 --> 00:51:18,241
Vince McMahon, when he can't draw
the crowd that he wants,

973
00:51:18,325 --> 00:51:19,868
he goes back to the familiar.

974
00:51:19,951 --> 00:51:22,996
The Ultimate Slime, Hulk Hogan.

975
00:51:23,080 --> 00:51:27,334
Sergeant Slaughter essentially
would turn into the Iron Sheik,

976
00:51:27,417 --> 00:51:30,337
wrestling Hulk Hogan at WrestleMania VII.

977
00:51:30,420 --> 00:51:32,631
Iraq invaded Kuwait.

978
00:51:32,714 --> 00:51:34,966
Shut your mouth, you pig!

979
00:51:35,050 --> 00:51:37,719
From an Iranian to the next big villain.

980
00:51:37,803 --> 00:51:41,223
And he's literally
doing the same identical match.

981
00:51:42,390 --> 00:51:44,351
It's not over yet!

982
00:51:44,434 --> 00:51:48,271
They should have found somebody
to take my place in the '90s, but didn't.

983
00:51:48,355 --> 00:51:50,607
-The cover!
-…two, one!

984
00:51:50,690 --> 00:51:51,817
He got him!

985
00:51:51,900 --> 00:51:54,569
-They couldn't replace Hogan.
-What a comeback!

986
00:51:54,653 --> 00:51:57,072
So they had
to put the belt back on me again.

987
00:52:01,660 --> 00:52:05,789
You know, my run was a lot longer
than Vince expected it to be.

988
00:52:05,872 --> 00:52:09,042
I ran with it as hard as I could
and as long as I could.

989
00:52:09,126 --> 00:52:14,214
Most guys' careers don't generate
that type of interest for that long.

990
00:52:14,756 --> 00:52:17,217
-Jesus.
-Anything good here?

991
00:52:17,300 --> 00:52:18,718
I've looked through there, see?

992
00:52:18,802 --> 00:52:21,429
Looks like there's contracts
and all kind of crap in there.

993
00:52:21,513 --> 00:52:23,390
Who knows? Could be anything.

994
00:52:24,724 --> 00:52:28,186
I want you to understand
that Hulkamania is never gonna die.

995
00:52:28,270 --> 00:52:31,815
It's something that is going to go down
in the history books as an era.

996
00:52:32,941 --> 00:52:34,985
You talk about the Roaring '20s still.

997
00:52:36,236 --> 00:52:38,697
Hulkamania era is going to be
talked about like that.

998
00:52:38,780 --> 00:52:42,951
You know, you talk about World War I,
World War II, the Wild Wild West.

999
00:52:43,034 --> 00:52:45,287
Hulkamania will be talked about like that.

1000
00:52:45,370 --> 00:52:47,372
It was a part of our society.

1001
00:52:48,206 --> 00:52:50,709
It was a part
of the international climate.

1002
00:52:50,792 --> 00:52:52,169
Write Hulk-a-Missile.

1003
